{"ID":270198, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"198\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs197.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs199.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 198<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">in the heavens,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and gave them their laws, conditions and bounds,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> which they cannot pass,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> except\n  by His commandments; they all move in perfect harmony in their sphere and order,<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> and are as\n  lights, wonders and signs unto us.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> The sea also has its bounds<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> which it cannot pass.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> God has set\n  many signs on the earth,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> as well as in the heavens; for instance, the oak of the forest,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> the fruit of\n  the tree,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> the herb of the field,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> all bear a sign that seed hath been planted there; for it is a decree\n  of the Lord<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> that every tree, plant, and herb bearing seed should bring forth of its kind,<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> and cannot\n  come forth after any other law or principle.<span class=\"textFootRef\">a<\/span> Upon the same principle do I contend that baptism is\n  a sign ordained of God, for the believer in Christ to take upon himself in order to enter into the\n  kingdom of God, &ldquo;for except ye are born of water and of the Spirit ye cannot enter into the Kingdom\n  of God,&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> said the Savior. It is a sign and a commandment which God has set for man to enter into\n  His kingdom. Those who seek to enter in any other way<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> will seek in vain; for God will not receive\n  them,<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> neither will the angels acknowledge their works as accepted,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> for they have not obeyed the\n  ordinances,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> nor attended to the signs which God ordained for the salvation of man, to prepare<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> him\n  for, and give him a title to, a celestial glory;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and God had decreed that all who will not obey His\n  voice<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> shall not escape the damnation of hell.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> What is the damnation of hell? To go with that\n  society who have not obeyed His commands.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Baptism and the Gift of the Holy Ghost<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Baptism is a sign to God, to angels, and to heaven that we do the will of God,<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> and there is no\n  other way<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> beneath the heavens<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> whereby God hath ordained for man to come to Him to be saved,<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span>\n  and enter into the Kingdom of God, except faith in Jesus Christ, repentance, and baptism for the\n  remission of sins, and any other course is in vain;<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> then you have the promise of the gift of the Holy\n  Ghost.<span class=\"footRef\">29<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">What is the sign of the healing of the sick? The laying on of hands is the sign or way marked\n  out by James,<span class=\"footRef\">30<\/span> and the custom of the ancient Saints as ordered by the Lord, and we<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106274\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106274)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106274)\">Deut. 4:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115779\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115779)\">&nbs